post_text: After graduating from Veritas as a part of the founding class, Xavier attended Hampden Charter School of Science, where he is currently a senior. Throughout his time at HCSS, he participated in Robotics Club, the National Honor Society, Student Council, and his favorite sport Wrestling. Xavier shared with us “ I remember at Veritas I always wanted to be an engineer so when I entered high school, I took the classes necessary and now I plan on majoring in Mechanical Engineering at Columbia University.” Help us congratulate Xavier on his college plans !

post_text: Park Rangers from Springfield Armory came to 5th grade to do a presentation about Shay's Rebellion-- which happened right here in Springfield in 1786. Scholars have been learning about the formation of our government after the American Revolution in History class. As a part of the program scholars "became" a person from US history and learned about their role in Shay's Rebellion. They then worked in groups and participated in a mock trial in order to determine who was most at fault for this rebellion: the farmers, the state government officials or the federal government officials and the founding fathers. #edthataddsup #history #springfield #parkrangers

post_text:
Why be an Associate Teacher at Veritas? Hear from our amazing 8th grade Associate Teacher, Victoria Rowe!
>>>>>>> master

"I decided to be an Associate Teacher because I thought it the perfect opportunity for me to learn as much as I can about teaching before being given a whole classroom. I was especially interested in Veritas because of the constant coaching and checking-in to make sure teachers are at their best. Thus far, my favorite experience has been developing relationships with Veritas students...it is much like a family here and I am happy to be a part of it."

To learn more about the Associate Teacher Program, email recruitment@vpcs.org. #talenttuesday #teachertuesday #eddthataddsup

Families & Students,

It is with sincere excitement that I welcome both students and families to our Veritas community for the 19-20 school year! We are ready to do everything it takes to set your scholars towards a path of immense success at high school, college, and beyond. We know that to do this, we need the voices of our families and our students to shine through more than ever. Though most of your communication through the year will be with our outstanding teachers who support your scholars every day, I extend the invitation to collaborate with me directly around anything you think will make our school a better place.

In partnership towards the success of our scholars,

Amy Clark,…

Join us for dinner at Chipotle in Chicopee on Tuesday, March 13th between 4:00pm and 8:00pm! 50% of proceeds will be given to the school to support our 8th grade trip to Washington, DC.

Bring in this flyer, show it on your smartphone or tell the cashier you’re supporting the cause to make sure that 50% of the proceeds
will be donated to our 8th Grade DC Trip.

We need you to make this fundraiser a great success and we promise good food and lots of fun!
